  "tutorial.step1.title": "Welcome",
  "tutorial.step1.text": "Let's set up a camp together. We start with the ground area, then place a tent. Press ESC any time to abort.",
  "tutorial.step2.title": "Step 1: Ground tool",
  "tutorial.step2.text": "ALWAYS start with the ground area – this defines your camp boundary. Click the hexagon icon (ground area) now.",
  "tutorial.step3.title": "Step 2: Draw the area",
  "tutorial.step3.text": "Click on the canvas to place corner points. Double-click or Enter closes the polygon. You can adjust it later anytime.",
  "tutorial.step4.title": "Step 3a: Pick a tent",
  "tutorial.step4.text": "Pick a tent from the object palette on the left (single click).",
  "tutorial.step4b.title": "Step 3b: Place the tent",
  "tutorial.step4b.text": "Now click on the canvas (ideally inside your ground area) to place it. The place tool stays active so you can drop more tents in a row.",
  "tutorial.step5.title": "Properties",
  "tutorial.step5.text": "When you select an object its properties appear here on the right (name, size, color, guy ropes, entrance, etc.). Multi-select with Ctrl/Cmd+Click.",
  "tutorial.step6.title": "Placed objects",
  "tutorial.step6.text": "All placed objects appear here. The magnifier opens a search field; double-click an entry to zoom to that object.",
  "tutorial.step7.title": "Layers",
  "tutorial.step7.text": "Organize objects in layers (e.g. sleeping tents, functional area). Layers can be hidden or locked.",
  "tutorial.step8.title": "Tabs / camps",
  "tutorial.step8.text": "Use multiple tabs for different camps or variants. Right-click a tab for export, duplicate etc.",
  "tutorial.step9.title": "Tools",
  "tutorial.step9.text": "Switch between select, pan, ground, area, fence, text, measure and more here. Shortcuts live in the settings.",
  "tutorial.step10.title": "IMPORTANT: Save & export",
  "tutorial.step10.text": "Auto-save only stores locally in your browser! For REAL backups use the Export function (top right) – save your camp as JSON, print it or export as PNG/SVG.",
  "tutorial.step11.title": "Settings",
  "tutorial.step11.text": "The gear icon hides grid, language, display options, shortcuts — and lets you restart this tutorial.",
  "tutorial.step12.title": "Done!",
  "tutorial.step12.text": "That's it. Remember: use Export for real backups! Bug reports and links live in the footer. Have fun planning!",
